
[1]commencement

   COMMENCEMENT, n.

   1. Beginning; rise; origin; first existence; as the commencement of New
   Style in 1752; the commencement of hostilities in 1775.

   2. The time when students in colleges commence bachelors; a day in
   which degrees are publicly conferred on students who have finished a
   collegiate education. In Cambridge, Eng., the day when masters of arts
   and doctors complete their degrees.
